==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Porphyritic
<hw>Por`phy*rit"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>porphyritique</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Relating to, or
resembling, porphyry, that is, characterized by the presence of distinct
crystals, as of feldspar, quartz, or augite, in a relatively
fine-grained base, often aphanitic or cryptocrystalline.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Porphyrization</ent>⟦br⟧
